This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with policy optimization in Markov Decision Processes (MDPs) which is a common problem in reinforcement learning. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as MDPs are a fundamental concept in AI. Additionally, the paper discusses optimization methods for robotics applications, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with control systems, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses convergence guarantees and performance guarantees, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
